"# Chapter 14 — Composer introspection: widget round-trip is introspection too

A composer canvas is a live rendering of a Scheme form. Move a slider, the form updates. Change a value in the form, the slider follows. That two-way binding is a flavor of introspection you have not seen yet — the form is queryable from the widgets and the widgets are queryable from the form.

This chapter shows how the composer's round-trip is an introspection surface.

## 14.1 The composer canvas

A composer canvas binds to a target form:

```scheme
(composer/canvas (:bind '(cart/main))
  (composer/slider :label \"BPM\" :bind '(cart/main :bpm) :min 60 :max 240 :step 1)
  (composer/piano-roll :bind '(cart/main :song) :range '(C3 . C6) :steps 32))
```

The canvas has one slider and one piano-roll. Both are bound to paths inside the target form.

## 14.2 composer/emit — canvas to form

`composer/emit` walks the canvas and produces the current form.

```scheme
(composer/emit my-canvas)
;; => (cart/main :bpm 120 :song (sequence (note ...) ...))
```

The return is Scheme. Readable. Runnable. This is the canvas asked *what form do you produce right now?*.

## 14.3 composer/apply — form to canvas

`composer/apply` walks the canvas and updates each widget's state to match a form.

```scheme
(composer/apply my-canvas '(cart/main :bpm 180 :song (sequence (note :pitch 'C4))))
;; canvas widgets update: slider now shows 180, piano-roll shows one note
```

This is the canvas asked *update your widgets to match this form*.

## 14.4 The round-trip guarantee

`(composer/apply c (composer/emit c))` is identity. Emit the form. Apply the form. Everything ends up in the same state.

This guarantee is what makes the composer trustworthy. Save the emitted form to disk. Reload later. Apply. You are exactly where you left off. No lossy serialization. No hidden state.

## 14.5 Widgets are introspectable

Each widget carries metadata. You can query the canvas for its widgets:

```scheme
(composer/widgets my-canvas)
;; => (:slider :piano-roll)

(composer/widget-info my-canvas :slider)
;; => (:label \"BPM\" :bind (cart/main :bpm) :min 60 :max 240 :step 1 :current 120)
```

Every widget's current bound value, its label, its config — all queryable.

