## 14.17 A worked example

You build a composer for a synth patch.

```scheme
(define c
  (composer/canvas (:bind '(synth))
    (composer/slider :label \"Attack\" :bind '(synth :env :a) :min 0 :max 2 :step 0.01)
    (composer/slider :label \"Decay\" :bind '(synth :env :d) :min 0 :max 2 :step 0.01)
    (composer/slider :label \"Sustain\" :bind '(synth :env :s) :min 0 :max 1 :step 0.01)
    (composer/slider :label \"Release\" :bind '(synth :env :r) :min 0 :max 4 :step 0.01)))
```

Emit:

```scheme
(composer/emit c)
;; => (synth :env (:a 0.01 :d 0.1 :s 0.7 :r 0.5))
```

Save:

```scheme
(composer/save c \"my-patch.slat\")
```

The file on disk is the emitted form. Next session load and apply:

```scheme
(define c2 (composer/load \"my-patch.slat\"))
(composer/emit c2)
;; => (synth :env (:a 0.01 :d 0.1 :s 0.7 :r 0.5))   ;; identical
```

Round-trip preserved. No composer-specific serialization. Just Scheme forms and the composer's emit/apply pair.

